<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-508-660  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 508 660.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  May 14 1990 v4 n19 p10(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>AF widens scope of AFAMPS. (Air Force; Air Forces Advanced MissionPlanning System)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Poos, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An automated mission planning system designed for the Air Force'sTactical Air Command will be made available to the Strategic Airand Military Airlift commands as well, doubling the cost of thesystem.andP;  Originally called the Tactical Air Forces AdvancedMission Planning System, it will now be know as the Air ForceAdvanced Mission Planning System (AFAMPS) to indicate theinclusion of the other two commands.andP;  The original cost estimateof $100 million has been raised to $200 million.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     WeaponsMilitaryGovernment ContractsUnited States. Air Force.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>